  "texts": [
    "S1, we project the original labeled text, the augmented text using back translation, and the hidden vector obtained by the SoftMix operation, respectively.",
    "It can be seen that the augmented text is close to the original text, which means that the back translation operation brings limited diversity to the training corpus.",
    "Then, for the gray nodes projected by the hidden cases generated by the SoftMix operation, they are farther away from both the original document and the augmentation in the input space, and are more dispersed in the latent space.",
    "This indicates that the SoftMix operation can generate more diverse and informative representations compared with the input space augmentation, potentially leading to improved model performance.",
    "Comparison with RemixMatch baseline."
  ],
